Class ReturnObjectImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • ReturnObjectImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReturnObject

    public class ReturnObjectImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements ReturnObject
    A wrapper containing either an object (the result of an operation on a data structure) or an error value. Original interface by PiJ team. Implemented by Chris Grocott for Coursework 2. October 2015

    • Constructor Detail

      • ReturnObjectImpl

        public ReturnObjectImpl(java.lang.Object wrappedObj,
                ErrorMessage error)
        Two argument constructor for ReturnObjectImpl. Setters have not been included so the only way to set the instance variables is to pass in parameters when the ReturnObjectImpl is instantiated. This is handled within the code returning a ReturnObject.
        Parameters:
        wrappedObj - the object to be wrapped by the new ReturnObjectImpl object
        error - the Error Message associated with the ReturnObjectImpl object

        public ErrorMessage getError()

        Specified by:

      • getReturnValue

        public java.lang.Object getReturnValue()
        Returns the object wrapped in this ReturnObject, i.e. the result of the operation if it was successful, or null if there has been error. Note that the output of this method must be null if hasError returns true, but the opposite is not true: if hasError returns false, this method may or may not return null.
        Specified by:
        getReturnValue in interface ReturnObject
        Returns:
        the return value from the method or null if there has been an error

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a String describing the wrapped object. The String returned is the same as if the toString() method were called on the wrapped object directly.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a String describing the wrapped object, if the wrapped object is null then the string 'NULL' is returned
